valuation_comment.en:
At the current price of KRW 650,000, the PER is 35.8x and the PBR is 7.02x (self-calculated, with EPS of KRW 18,150 and BPS of KRW 92,561). Compared with the loss-making 2022 or the 1–5% operating-margin years of 2023–2024, today's PER and PBR — set against normalized profits — are markedly higher than past levels. In an industry context, the valuation sits above peers and the broader industrials sector; 
one brokerage applied a 37x PER for this year, the same as peers, while also citing the industrials sector's average valuation of 49x.
 This suggests the multiple reflects both the shipbuilding upcycle and expectations for new businesses such as data-center engines. On dividends, the dividend per share is KRW 5,661 and the yield is 0.87% (official KRX figures), a low level closer to a growth-stock profile. Ultimately, the current valuation can be read as a zone whose justification hinges on whether future orders, capacity additions and profit growth meet expectations.
